[gun clicks]

819
00:55:27,421 --> 00:55:30,301
[menacing music continues]

820
00:55:39,381 --> 00:55:43,221
[body sliding]

821
00:55:48,981 --> 00:55:49,620
[trunk door slams]

822
00:55:49,621 --> 00:55:52,581
[engine humming]

823
00:56:00,301 --> 00:56:03,061
[engine revs, idling]

824
00:56:04,341 --> 00:56:07,221
[menacing music continues]

825
00:56:11,221 --> 00:56:12,021
[car door slams]

826
00:56:14,541 --> 00:56:15,461
[trunk door opens]

827
00:56:16,621 --> 00:56:17,901
- [gun clicks]
- [Doug winces]

828
00:56:18,581 --> 00:56:21,461
[grunts] Motherfuck...

829
00:56:21,821 --> 00:56:23,981
[panting]

830
00:56:24,461 --> 00:56:27,341
[footfalls on gravel]

831
00:56:38,901 --> 00:56:40,781
[body thumps, scrapes]

832
00:56:46,461 --> 00:56:49,341
[panting]

833
00:56:52,901 --> 00:56:54,221
What were you doing
at my house?

834
00:56:54,461 --> 00:56:55,261
[gulps]

835
00:56:57,061 --> 00:56:58,061
[sniffles]

836
00:57:00,301 --> 00:57:02,221
[shouts] What were you doing
at my house?!

837
00:57:04,141 --> 00:57:07,900
Yeah, I expect honest answers...

838
00:57:07,901 --> 00:57:10,101
...pointing guns at people.

839
00:57:13,181 --> 00:57:15,101
What about your boss?
What does he know about me?

840
00:57:16,341 --> 00:57:17,061
Not much.

841
00:57:18,541 --> 00:57:19,420
Not yet.

842
00:57:19,421 --> 00:57:22,620
[wind howling]

843
00:57:22,621 --> 00:57:23,941
You could just leave...

844
00:57:25,221 --> 00:57:30,301
...skip town, and none of this
will be your problem.

845
00:57:31,541 --> 00:57:33,380
Yeah, what about her?
I just leave her to you?

846
00:57:33,381 --> 00:57:35,421
You don't even know
who you're defending.

847
00:57:36,461 --> 00:57:41,020
It's a shame. [cackles]

848
00:57:41,021 --> 00:57:42,501
You're such a child.

849
00:57:42,981 --> 00:57:47,701
[mocking laughter]

850
00:57:50,981 --> 00:57:51,781
[gun clicks]

851
00:57:52,261 --> 00:57:53,220
- [gunshot echoes]
- [phone buzzes]

852
00:57:53,221 --> 00:57:54,220
[lipstick clasps]

853
00:57:54,221 --> 00:57:55,581
[phone buzzes]

854
00:57:57,141 --> 00:57:57,941
Hello?

855
00:57:58,101 --> 00:57:59,061
[Cole] I'm in.

856
00:57:59,541 --> 00:58:01,380
But I need to know if what you said
is even possible.

857
00:58:01,381 --> 00:58:02,301
Are you okay?

858
00:58:02,941 --> 00:58:03,901
[Cole] How soon can you meet?

859
00:58:04,661 --> 00:58:05,580
[door creaks open]

860
00:58:05,581 --> 00:58:06,461
Hey

861
00:58:08,101 --> 00:58:09,421
If what you said is true...

862
00:58:09,661 --> 00:58:12,300
...if Bilson actually has
that much money at his house...

863
00:58:12,301 --> 00:58:15,541
...then we need
to find a way in.

864
00:58:16,381 --> 00:58:17,421
I don't steal cash.

865
00:58:17,861 --> 00:58:19,781
I don't do B&E, so...

866
00:58:20,221 --> 00:58:21,661
Well, can you hack
into someone's phone?

867
00:58:21,981 --> 00:58:23,621
Yeah. Sure.

868
00:58:24,741 --> 00:58:26,781
Bilson's entire house
is connected to his phone.

869
00:58:28,301 --> 00:58:29,061
Um, okay.

870
00:58:30,741 --> 00:58:31,741
So...

871
00:58:33,261 --> 00:58:35,261
Here's how we need to play it.
You need to call him.

872
00:58:35,541 --> 00:58:38,021
[phone buzzes]

873
00:58:39,741 --> 00:58:41,100
- Yeah?
- It's me.

874
00:58:41,101 --> 00:58:42,220
Say you want
to see him again.

875
00:58:42,221 --> 00:58:43,620
Tell him you have the rest
of his money...

876
00:58:43,621 --> 00:58:45,580
...and you want to make
things right.

877
00:58:45,581 --> 00:58:47,301
[Sarah] I was thinking
we’d start over.

878
00:58:48,021 --> 00:58:51,300
I really miss you
and I want to fix things.

879
00:58:51,301 --> 00:58:52,540
Can I see you, please?

880
00:58:52,541 --> 00:58:53,621
What did you have in mind?

881
00:58:54,341 --> 00:58:55,621
[Sarah] We can start
with something easy.

882
00:58:56,661 --> 00:58:57,941
Usual place, usual time.

883
00:58:59,101 --> 00:59:00,141
You have the rest of it?

884
00:59:00,501 --> 00:59:01,301
Yes, I do.

885
00:59:01,751 --> 00:59:02,551
Fine.

886
00:59:03,141 --> 00:59:05,260
We're going to need to make
an exact copy of his phone...

887
00:59:05,261 --> 00:59:06,300
...in order to break
into his house...

888
00:59:06,301 --> 00:59:08,740
...so his security system
can't tell the difference...

889
00:59:08,741 --> 00:59:10,980
...which means we're going to
have to get our hands on it...

890
00:59:10,981 --> 00:59:11,860
...without him knowing.

891
00:59:11,861 --> 00:59:13,860
And that part's really important...

892
00:59:13,861 --> 00:59:15,660
...because if he feels like
it's been messed with...

893
00:59:15,661 --> 00:59:17,980
...if he gets suspicious
even for a second...

894
00:59:17,981 --> 00:59:19,821
...calls his service provider,
we're busted.

895
00:59:20,501 --> 00:59:21,420
And we're going to
have to do all of that...

896
00:59:21,421 --> 00:59:22,541
...within a really short window...

897
00:59:23,621 --> 00:59:25,701
...which means we're going to have
to get someone else to help us.

898
00:59:26,661 --> 00:59:31,461
[tense, dramatic music]

899
00:59:34,221 --> 00:59:35,341
[banging on door]

900
00:59:44,181 --> 00:59:45,861
[door creaks open]

901
00:59:50,701 --> 00:59:51,421
[door creaks closed]

902
00:59:59,661 --> 01:00:00,820
So what's the plan?
You're gonna...

903
01:00:00,821 --> 01:00:03,621
you’re gonna break
into this dude's house? [scoffs]

904
01:00:06,141 --> 01:00:07,421
Oh, man, why?

905
01:00:07,581 --> 01:00:09,540
That's none of your business, is it?

906
01:00:09,541 --> 01:00:13,381
Okay, I'm not helping you
or you, I'm good.

907
01:00:17,421 --> 01:00:19,821
How about another 500K
to get you past the million mark?

908
01:00:23,501 --> 01:00:26,661
All you'd be at worst is a doorman
that returns a lost cell phone.

909
01:00:27,581 --> 01:00:29,341
It's an awful lot of pay
for next to nothing.

910
01:00:34,021 --> 01:00:38,380
[menacing music]

911
01:00:38,381 --> 01:00:41,380
If this goes bad and
somebody starts stabbing up...

912
01:00:41,381 --> 01:00:44,260
...you and your little girlfriend
here in the restaurant...

913
01:00:44,261 --> 01:00:47,221
I'm just going to
stand there and watch.

914
01:00:54,941 --> 01:00:57,541
[engine rumbling]

915
01:01:01,101 --> 01:01:05,901
[menacing music]

916
01:01:07,421 --> 01:01:08,581
[phone buzzes]

917
01:01:19,341 --> 01:01:22,221
[menacing music]

918
01:01:25,541 --> 01:01:28,620
[engine humming]

919
01:01:28,621 --> 01:01:29,461
I missed you.

920
01:01:31,221 --> 01:01:33,421
The rest of my money, where is it?

921
01:01:33,661 --> 01:01:34,781
You said you'd have it.

922
01:01:35,861 --> 01:01:38,741
[menacing music]

923
01:01:45,021 --> 01:01:46,421
Account transfer info.

924
01:01:47,021 --> 01:01:48,141
Just like last time.

925
01:01:50,221 --> 01:01:51,381
I told you I had it.

926
01:01:53,541 --> 01:01:54,381
Yeah, we'll see.

927
01:01:54,981 --> 01:01:55,981
Come on, Mark.

928
01:01:57,181 --> 01:01:58,420
I'm not giving back
what was stolen...

929
01:01:58,421 --> 01:01:59,941
I'm covering the loss.

930
01:02:00,421 --> 01:02:03,301
[engine rumbling]

931
01:02:07,021 --> 01:02:07,860
[seatbelt clicks]

932
01:02:07,861 --> 01:02:08,621
Hey.

933
01:02:10,661 --> 01:02:11,741
You look so hot tonight.

934
01:02:11,981 --> 01:02:12,741
[scoffs]

935
01:02:13,901 --> 01:02:15,021
Let's talk inside.

936
01:02:19,381 --> 01:02:20,660
[car door closes, opens]

937
01:02:20,661 --> 01:02:23,180
[uneasy music]

938
01:02:23,181 --> 01:02:24,061
Thank you.

939
01:02:24,781 --> 01:02:25,661
[car door slams]

940
01:02:26,181 --> 01:02:28,741
[keys jingling]

941
01:02:32,701 --> 01:02:33,701
[car door opens]

942
01:02:38,141 --> 01:02:40,981
[utensils clinks]

943
01:02:41,501 --> 01:02:44,380
[rousing music]

944
01:02:44,381 --> 01:02:45,981
[cricket chirping]

945
01:02:52,421 --> 01:02:53,261
[vape hissing]

946
01:03:00,141 --> 01:03:03,981
[hushed chatter]
[tense music]

947
01:03:06,381 --> 01:03:07,061
[back door slams]

948
01:03:15,221 --> 01:03:16,181
And for you, ma'am?

949
01:03:16,661 --> 01:03:17,821
Gin and tonic, please.

950
01:03:18,021 --> 01:03:18,981
[softly] Thank you.

951
01:03:24,541 --> 01:03:25,381
Hi.

952
01:03:26,141 --> 01:03:28,261
- [relieved sigh]
- [drink pouring]

953
01:03:35,901 --> 01:03:37,381
[keyboard clacking]

954
01:03:39,781 --> 01:03:40,581
[laptop chimes]

955
01:03:43,261 --> 01:03:45,580
[tense music]

956
01:03:45,581 --> 01:03:47,541
[vape hissing]

957
01:03:48,341 --> 01:03:51,501
In my business,
people try to betray me.

958
01:03:52,461 --> 01:03:56,061
But I don't let them
because if they did, I pay.

959
01:03:56,621 --> 01:03:57,741
My family pays.

960
01:03:59,301 --> 01:04:00,701
I care about you very much.

961
01:04:01,861 --> 01:04:03,021
And that makes you a liability.

962
01:04:03,461 --> 01:04:05,420
And if anything ever
happened to you...

963
01:04:05,421 --> 01:04:07,021
I would be very, very sad.

964
01:04:08,581 --> 01:04:11,661
Nothing is going to
happen to me.

965
01:04:13,021 --> 01:04:14,100
I'm right here.

966
01:04:14,101 --> 01:04:15,941
[menacing music]

967
01:04:27,581 --> 01:04:30,021
[menacing music continues]

968
01:04:40,061 --> 01:04:43,141
[gate beeps, rattling]

969
01:04:49,381 --> 01:04:54,181
[menacing music continues]

970
01:04:55,661 --> 01:04:58,141
Can we please start over?

971
01:05:03,981 --> 01:05:04,701
[paper rustles]

972
01:05:05,221 --> 01:05:06,221
[knife clatters]

973
01:05:11,541 --> 01:05:12,821
- [gulps]
- [ice cube clinks]

974
01:05:16,461 --> 01:05:17,341
Oh.

975
01:05:19,661 --> 01:05:20,461
[sighs]

976
01:05:21,021 --> 01:05:22,021
[paper rustles]

977
01:05:22,901 --> 01:05:24,181
[menacing music]

978
01:05:25,141 --> 01:05:26,901
[distant chatter]

979
01:05:31,821 --> 01:05:34,620
[foreboding music]

980
01:05:34,621 --> 01:05:35,741
[keyboard clacking]

981
01:05:37,541 --> 01:05:41,181
[automated voice] House disarmed.
Front door unlocked.

982
01:05:42,821 --> 01:05:45,701
[tense rhythmic music]

983
01:06:06,101 --> 01:06:08,900
[crickets chirping]

984
01:06:08,901 --> 01:06:10,941
[soft footfalls]

985
01:06:15,261 --> 01:06:16,061
[door opens]

986
01:06:22,261 --> 01:06:24,060
[paper rustles]

987
01:06:24,061 --> 01:06:26,861
Yes. Let's... start over.

988
01:06:29,461 --> 01:06:32,541
Unless you're not
being honest with me.

989
01:06:32,741 --> 01:06:33,461
I...

990
01:06:35,021 --> 01:06:36,701
I have always been honest with you.

991
01:06:37,701 --> 01:06:39,221
- Have you?
- I have.

992
01:06:39,901 --> 01:06:42,221
Because the people I owe money to...

993
01:06:43,781 --> 01:06:45,941
my commitment is to them.

994
01:06:46,301 --> 01:06:48,741
Just like my commitment
is to my family

995
01:06:49,501 --> 01:06:51,461
My commitment to you.

996
01:06:52,541 --> 01:06:55,421
[foreboding music]

997
01:06:57,501 --> 01:06:58,701
I would never betray you.

998
01:06:59,621 --> 01:07:00,541
I wouldn't.

999
01:07:01,541 --> 01:07:03,621
I can see that. Now...

1000
01:07:06,421 --> 01:07:09,301
[crickets chirping]

1001
01:07:34,701 --> 01:07:35,581
[taps on keyboard]

1002
01:07:38,781 --> 01:07:39,901
[laptop chimes]

1003
01:07:43,981 --> 01:07:45,301
- [laptop chimes]
- [chuckles]

1004
01:07:50,781 --> 01:07:53,500
[keypad beeps]

1005
01:07:53,501 --> 01:07:54,861
[safe clangs, whirs]

1006
01:07:56,181 --> 01:07:58,021
[door opens]

1007
01:08:03,701 --> 01:08:04,421
[laptop thuds]

1008
01:08:07,101 --> 01:08:07,901
[cabinet opens]

1009
01:08:15,341 --> 01:08:16,140
[drawer opens]

1010
01:08:16,141 --> 01:08:19,101
[rousing music]

1011
01:08:24,701 --> 01:08:25,501
[zipper unzips]

1012
01:08:35,301 --> 01:08:37,621
This will be hard
for me with you.

1013
01:08:38,301 --> 01:08:39,101
So hard.

1014
01:08:40,621 --> 01:08:41,861
It's going to take time.

1015
01:08:43,501 --> 01:08:45,861
But my job, as you know...

1016
01:08:47,421 --> 01:08:48,981
...it being what it is...

1017
01:08:54,181 --> 01:08:55,021
What's wrong?

1018
01:08:56,541 --> 01:08:58,501
[tuts] My phone.

1019
01:08:59,261 --> 01:08:59,941
What about it?

1020
01:09:00,341 --> 01:09:01,101
I don't have it.

1021
01:09:04,701 --> 01:09:05,581
[back door clangs]

1022
01:09:06,141 --> 01:09:07,500
[back door creaks]
[back door slams shut]

1023
01:09:07,501 --> 01:09:08,980
Maybe you left it in the car.

1024
01:09:08,981 --> 01:09:10,940
I didn't leave it in the car.
I had it when I...

1025
01:09:10,941 --> 01:09:13,341
- [hurried footsteps]
- [utensils clattering]

1026
01:09:15,341 --> 01:09:17,020
- You sit.
- Okay.

1027
01:09:17,021 --> 01:09:18,261
[male voice] Mr. Bilson.

1028
01:09:18,501 --> 01:09:20,781
Sorry, I believe you left
your phone outside.

1029
01:09:24,221 --> 01:09:26,821
[tuts] Yes. That is my phone.

1030
01:09:29,021 --> 01:09:31,101
Thank you.
Tell me your name again.

1031
01:09:31,421 --> 01:09:32,021
Oscar.

1032
01:09:32,501 --> 01:09:33,341
Thank you, Oscar.

1033
01:09:33,941 --> 01:09:35,061
I'll make sure to find you later.

1034
01:09:36,021 --> 01:09:36,900
[zipper zipping]

1035
01:09:36,901 --> 01:09:39,220
[dramatic music]

1036
01:09:39,221 --> 01:09:40,101
[zipper zips]

1037
01:09:43,741 --> 01:09:44,541
[zipper zipping]

1038
01:09:57,381 --> 01:09:58,101
[bag slumps]

1039
01:10:01,901 --> 01:10:05,340
[dramatic music intensifies]

1040
01:10:05,341 --> 01:10:06,340
[car trunk slams]

1041
01:10:06,341 --> 01:10:08,020
- [car beeps]
- [keys jingling]

1042
01:10:08,021 --> 01:10:10,981
[building crescendo]

1043
01:10:14,221 --> 01:10:15,021
[door slams]

1044
01:10:16,461 --> 01:10:19,501
[panting]

1045
01:10:21,581 --> 01:10:22,781
[sighs]

1046
01:10:24,421 --> 01:10:25,861
[door creaks open]

1047
01:10:32,821 --> 01:10:33,701
[Oscar whispers] Hey.

1048
01:10:34,501 --> 01:10:35,861
- Hey.
- [chuckles]

1049
01:10:39,021 --> 01:10:40,821
[smooches]

1050
01:10:45,301 --> 01:10:48,661
Almost there.
We're almost there.

1051
01:10:50,941 --> 01:10:52,861
Oscar, he's acting like a psycho.

1052
01:10:53,781 --> 01:10:55,540
I don't think he believes
a single fucking word I'm saying.

1053
01:10:55,541 --> 01:10:56,900
Look, Cole has the money.

1054
01:10:56,901 --> 01:10:58,180
I'll go take care of him.

1055
01:10:58,181 --> 01:10:59,061
That's it.

1056
01:10:59,341 --> 01:11:00,421
[whispers]
Let's just not hurt him.

1057
01:11:01,501 --> 01:11:03,021
Let's just get the money and go.

1058
01:11:03,181 --> 01:11:04,141
[soft chuckle]

1059
01:11:08,221 --> 01:11:12,061
[rousing music]

1060
01:11:12,541 --> 01:11:14,621
Oscar. Oscar.

1061
01:11:25,741 --> 01:11:27,220
[dramatic music]

1062
01:11:27,221 --> 01:11:28,700
[car approaching]

1063
01:11:28,701 --> 01:11:30,341
[panting] Fuck!

1064
01:11:31,981 --> 01:11:34,861
[dramatic music intensifies]

1065
01:11:39,461 --> 01:11:40,261
[bag slumps]

1066
01:11:42,061 --> 01:11:44,941
[dramatic music continues]

1067
01:11:48,061 --> 01:11:48,781
[light system whirs]

1068
01:12:01,301 --> 01:12:02,101
[bag slumps]

1069
01:12:07,701 --> 01:12:09,580
Thought I left the alarm on.

1070
01:12:09,581 --> 01:12:10,501
Hello?

1071
01:12:11,821 --> 01:12:15,581
[building crescendo]

1072
01:12:18,541 --> 01:12:19,301
[wife] What?

1073
01:12:44,821 --> 01:12:45,701
You all right?

1074
01:12:50,461 --> 01:12:53,301
[tense music]

1075
01:13:01,261 --> 01:13:02,140
[bag slumps]

1076
01:13:02,141 --> 01:13:03,021
[trunk thumps]

1077
01:13:08,341 --> 01:13:09,301
[sighs]

1078
01:13:12,861 --> 01:13:15,981
[foreboding music]

1079
01:13:23,421 --> 01:13:25,301
The center console. Open it.

1080
01:13:28,741 --> 01:13:31,101
[object clatters]

1081
01:13:32,661 --> 01:13:33,581
Really, Mark?

1082
01:13:35,341 --> 01:13:36,461
Yes, really.

1083
01:13:39,381 --> 01:13:42,300
[phone buzzes]

1084
01:13:42,301 --> 01:13:43,141
